# ⚙️ Setup & Installation Guide

This guide will help you set up and run the project locally.

---

## 📌 Prerequisites

Make sure you have:

- Node.js (v14 or above)
- Python (v3.8 or above)
- pip (Python package manager)
- A modern browser (Chrome recommended)
- VS Code (optional)

---

## 📥 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd RESTAPI

🟢 2. Run JavaScript Backend (Express.js)
cd js-backend
npm install
npm start

Server will run on:
http://localhost:3000

🔵 3. Run Python Backend (FastAPI)
cd python-backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py

Server will run on:
http://localhost:8000

Swagger Docs:
http://localhost:8000/docs

🌐 4. Run Frontend

Open this file in your browser:

frontend/index.html

Tip: Use Live Server (VS Code extension) for better experience.

🔄 5. Switching Backends

You can switch between:

Express (port 3000)
FastAPI (port 8000)


✅ 6. Verify Setup

Try:
Adding a student
Updating a record
Deleting a student

If everything works, setup is complete.
